details:
Case 62 is a 44 year-old female Singapore Citizen with no recent travel history to China. She is linked to the cluster at Grace Assembly of God.

She reported onset of symptoms on 9 February, and sought treatment at a GP clinic the next day. She went to SGH on 12 February and was immediately isolated. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 13 February afternoon.

Prior to hospital admission, she reported that he had mostly stayed at home at Tanjong Pagar Road, except to seek medical treatment.
